sequenceDiagram
    participant Konflux as Konflux Build System<br/>Tekton PipelineRuns
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator<br/>Platform Operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>(JupyterLab/code-server/RStudio)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant NotebookCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller

    Note over Konflux,Registry: Flow 1: Workbench Image Deployment

    Konflux->>Registry: Push built container images<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Account
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply kustomize manifests<br/>(create ImageStreams)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStream annotations<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC SSO
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>+ kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>Registry: kubelet pulls image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Pull secret

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Notebook Session

    User->>Gateway: Access notebook UI<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC cookie
    Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    KRBAC->>Notebook: Proxy to workbench<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (pod network)<br/>Auth: None (pre-authenticated)
    Notebook-->>KRBAC: Response (HTML/JSON/WebSocket)
    KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over Notebook,Registry: Flow 3: Runtime Egress (User-Initiated)

    Notebook->>Registry: pip install (user packages)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: None
    Note right of Notebook: Also: Git repos (443/TCP),<br/>S3 storage (443/TCP),<br/>MongoDB (27017/TCP),<br/>ODBC sources (varies)
